Describe the impacts of african americans in WWII?

The african americans were abused and discriminated from most of the population in the United States, which caused massive outrage
due to racial discrimination. After the civil rights movement however, the rights of african americans were restored (in the United
states) due to the first amendment and the first point in the Universal declaration of human rights.


What is the united nations?

the united nations is a board of different ambassadors to each country that meet in New York at their headquarters. The united nations
is a solution for peace and provides countries for expressing their views and opinions to other executives to prevent severe conflict
and outbreak. The UN was founded in 1945 at the end of world war II.

Article 2 human rights?

Article 2 states: Everyone is entitled to all the rights and freedoms set forth in this Declaration, without distinction of any kind,
such as race, colour, sex, language, religion, political or other opinion, national or social origin, property, birth or other 
status. This insists that any citizen of a country that has officially signed the declaration are entitled to all rights that are
set forth in the universal declaration of human rights.